<headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 17 at 2:24PM EDT  by NWS Blacksburg</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of western Roanoke,
south central Craig and northeastern Montgomery Counties through 315
PM EDT...
At 224 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Blacksburg, moving east at 15 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph and pea size hail.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.
Locations impacted include...
Blacksburg...
Christiansburg...
Shawsville...
Bent Mountain...
Catawba...
Mc Donalds Mill...
and Bradshaw.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.25 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
